The paper discusses adversarial attacks on Graph Neural Networks (GNNs), which are a popular deep learning framework for machine learning tasks over relational data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the paper discusses adversarial attacks. The paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with neural networks and their applications. Finally, the paper involves social and information networks (cs.SI) as it deals with relational data.
